gate: OPEN
task: S75-TC2
title: Apply Map Behavior Settings to ClusterMap (Names, Clustering, Geolocation)
description: |
  Three settings toggles must actually affect MapScreen runtime behavior.
  Currently they are persisted to localStorage (after TA2) but nothing reads them.

  1. "Show icons" (settings.vehicleArrowShow — API field):
     ClusterMap already renders vehicle markers. If vehicleArrowShow=false, hide
     vehicle arrow/icon and show only a dot or name label.
     Implementation: pass vehicleArrowShow from useSettingsStore to ClusterMap prop.
     ClusterMap should conditionally render arrow icon or fallback marker.

  2. "Object names" (local_show_names — localStorage via useLocalSettings):
     Show/hide vehicle name label on the map marker.
     Implementation: pass showNames prop to ClusterMap. When false, omit name label
     in marker tooltip/popup.

  3. "Group objects" (local_group_objects — localStorage via useLocalSettings):
     Enable/disable Leaflet marker clustering.
     ClusterMap likely uses MarkerClusterGroup. When local_group_objects=false,
     render plain Marker instances instead of a cluster group.
     Implementation: pass clusterEnabled prop to ClusterMap.

  4. "Geolocation" (local_show_geo — localStorage via useLocalSettings):
     Show/hide the user's own geolocation dot on the map.
     MapScreen already has a geoTrigger and handleGeolocate handler. The geolocation
     toggle should start/stop continuous location watching:
       - toggle ON: call navigator.geolocation.watchPosition, render user dot
       - toggle OFF: clearWatch, remove user dot from map
     Implementation: ClusterMap or MapScreen reads local_show_geo and auto-activates
     geolocation on mount if the setting is on.

  All four props should be read from their sources in MapScreen and passed down to
  ClusterMap. MapScreen should subscribe to useSettingsStore for vehicleArrowShow
  and to useLocalSettings for the other three.

acceptance:
  - Turning off "Show icons" in settings → vehicle arrows disappear from map
  - Turning off "Object names" → vehicle name labels disappear from map markers
  - Turning off "Group objects" → markers no longer cluster, each shown individually
  - Turning on "Geolocation" → blue dot appears at user's GPS position on map
  - All changes apply without requiring app restart or page reload

requires: [FRONTEND_DEV]
estimated: 3 hours
dep: S75-TA2
